pve-storage-ontap-nvmetcp (1.0-1) stable; urgency=medium

  * Initial release.
  * ONTAP REST API client for NVMe namespace, volume, subsystem,
    consistency group, and snapshot management (ONTAP 9.18+).
  * PVE storage plugin implementing APIVER 13:
    - alloc_image / free_image / list_images
    - volume snapshots via consistency groups (atomic multi-disk)
      with per-volume fallback
    - volume_resize / volume_size_info
    - qemu_blockdev_options (host_device driver)
    - volume_qemu_snapshot_method (storage-side)
    - on_add_hook / on_update_hook / on_delete_hook
    - sensitive-properties for password isolation
    - NVMe/TCP auto-discovery via ONTAP data LIFs
    - Three-strategy NVMe device resolution
      (ontapdevices, sysfs UUID, nvme-list)
  * Architecture: 1 VM disk = 1 NVMe namespace = 1 FlexVol volume.
  * Code formatted with proxmox-perltidy, follows Proxmox Perl
    Style Guide.

 -- Nicolas I. (McKay1717) <https://github.com/McKay1717>  Sun, 15 Feb 2026 18:00:00 +0100
